== Main Course ==

> The chocolate pots will take 2-3 hours to set so we'd recommend getting them prepared earlier in the day. However, they'll still be delicious if you only leave them in the fridge for a few minutes. Either way, make your pudding (all 3 steps) before you start cooking your main!

Preheat your #oven{} to 100°C. Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Chop the @tenderstem broccoli{150}(chopped into 3 pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated). Pick the @sage{½}(leaves picked off their stalks). Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #clingfilm{}, pop on a #cutting board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a saucepan until it's 1-2cm thick all over.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on medium high heat and add drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Reserve 2 of the largest sage leaves per person. Once the oil is hot, pop the rest of the sage leaves in your pan in a single layer. Fry until crispy, ~{1-2%mins}. Remove the leaves to a #bowl{} and set aside.

Pop your frying pan back on high heat and add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Season the chicken with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}, then place 2 sage leaves on each breast (the ones you reserved). And lay a rasher of @serrano ham{2}(rashed) flat over the top to cover one side. Once the oil is really hot, carefully lay in the chicken breasts ham side down and cook until browned and crispy, ~{5-6%mins}, turn down the heat if necessary. Turn and cook for ~{4-5%mins} on the other side. Once cooked, transfer to a #baking tray{}, cover with #foil{} and pop in your oven to keep warm.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Cook the chicken breasts in batches if you can't fit them all in the pan.

Pop the @fresh tagliatelle{200} and tenderstem broccoli into your boiling water and simmer until tender, ~{3-4%mins}. Drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan, drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Put your frying pan back on medium heat and add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Add the shallot and stir-fry until softened, ~{3-4%mins}. Stir in the garlic and cook, stirring for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @water{150%ml}(for the sauce) and @chicken stock powder{1}, bring to the boil and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%mins}. Vigorously stir in the @unsalted butter{30%g} until melted, then stir in the @creme fraiche{150} and bring to the boil. Then remove from the heat. Taste and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} if you feel it needs it.

Remove the chicken from your oven and place on a cutting board to rest for a couple of mins. Add the pasta to the sauce along with any meat resting juices, toss to combine.

> TIP: Add a splash of water too if the liquid has evaporated too much and reheat if necessary.

Divide the pasta between your bowls. Thinly slice the chicken and serve on top of the pasta with the crispy sage leaves dotted over the top. Serve immediately. Enjoy!

== Chocolate Pots ==

Pour the @coconut milk{200%ml} into a medium pan and pop onto medium high heat. Bring to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Remove from the heat and immediately add the @chocolate chips{100} and @salt{pinch}. Allow to sit for ~{1%minute}, then stir the coconut milk and chocolate together until the chocolate is melted and everything is completely combined.

Pour the coconut chocolate mixture into appropriately sized #glasses{} / #ramekins{}.

> TIP: Put these in the fridge at the beginning of the recipe if you're in a rush.

Cover with clingfilm and pop into the fridge to set - this will take ~{2-3%hours} if you want them fully set, but they'll still be delicious if you want to eat them immediately or straight after your main course.

== Maple Salted Nuts Topping ==

Remove and discard the shells from the @pistachios{25}(roughly chopped) and roughly chop. Heat a medium frying pan over medium heat (no oil!) Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15} and pistachios and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%mins}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, remove from the heat and add the @maple syrup{2} and @salt{pinch} to the pan. Stir together and transfer to a bowl. Once ready to serve, spoon the nuts on top of the chocolate pots and enjoy!